      "span_text": "For example, as illustrated in  , centroids can create difficulties for problems where communications or travel between points must take place within a specified network, since centroids may lie in unreachable areas such as rivers or fields that cannot be traversed, or may compel some points that lie in a centroid-based cluster to cross such areas to reach other cluster points, thus linking points that are not desirable to be grouped within a cluster together.",
